<br>
Lower the mob density as well on raids so that you can get done with these in 2 hours instead of 3 if you know what you're doing.<br>
<br>
Challenge = good.  Mindless slaughter of insignificant mobs while on a timer = bad.<br>
<br>
IMO loot is fine as a parallel suppliment for PoP progression.  Alot of the augments, top GoD guilds would still find useful. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=269698">Reynaldo</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://p201.ezboard.com/btheconcerthall.showUserPublicProfile?gid=reynaldofl>ReynaldoFL</A> at: 7/1/04 5:13 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#deddbf><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://p201.ezboard.com/btheconcerthall.showUserPublicProfile?gid=fflewddurfflam>Fflewddur Fflam</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Minstrel</span><br>  Posts: 979<br> <font color=#330000>(7/2/04 11:37 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://p201.ezboard.com/ftheconcerthallbackstage.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=19550.topic&index=23>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: *blink*</span><hr size=1> &quot;Honestly. Do you believe half of the stuff that you post?&quot;<br>
<br>
That was sarcasm.  All I really believe about uberguilds is that SoE's futile attempts to keep them challenged at the expense of the remaining 95% of the server populations is the reason why EQ's subscription rate is plummeting.  <br>
<br>
And again, the issue here is not &quot;I have a life&quot; versus &quot;I don't have a life&quot;, but rather that a game that wants to focus 100% on raiding ought to wake up and realize such a thing will not succeed unless every single time zone in the entire world has an equal opportunity.<br>
<br>
What time zone do you live in, by the way?  As a recent high school graduate, you were likely able to log in daily by 3pm in your timezone whenever you felt like it as it is, something that could further be compounded if you lived on the East Coast US or somewhere in Europe.  It's just another reason the LDoN raids should have been expanded to include all types of guild levels.<br>
<br>
-FF <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page <a href=http://p201.ezboard.com/ftheconcerthallbackstage.showMessageRange?topicID=19550.topic&start=1&stop=20>1</a> <b>2</b>  </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://p201.ezboard.com/ftheconcerthallbackstage.showPrevMessage?topicID=19550.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://p201.ezboard.com/ftheconcerthallbackstage.showNextMessage?topicID=19550.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://p201.ezboard.com/ftheconcerthallbackstage.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=19550.topic&index=23><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/traditional/addReply.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://p201.ezboard.com/ftheconcerthallbackstage.emailToFriend?topicID=19550.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://p201.ezboard.com/ftheconcerthallbackstage.threadControl?topicID=19550.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/traditional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://p201.ezboard.com/ftheconcerthallbackstage.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=19550.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/subscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to receive email notification of replies"> Click to receive email notification of replies</a> <br>  <a href=http://p201.ezboard.com/ftheconcerthallbackstage.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=19550.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/unsubscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to stop receiving email notification of replies"> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies</a> <br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></